From c412e781c7c8a0a41500fce6e14efc279c5a285d Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Balamurugan Ramar <quic_bramar@quicinc.com>
Date: Thu, 10 Apr 2025 23:26:51 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] mac80211: wifi Avoid linkid WARN_ON during recovery

During FW recovery, first vdev's get starts followed
by peer create. In case of AP+Monitor, monitor start
capturing before peer create completion but mac80211
have associated sta entry which leads to warn_on.
Add in_reconfig flag check for warn_on which points the
recovery state.

Signed-off-by: Yuvasree Sivasankaran <quic_ysivasan@quicinc.com>
Signed-off-by: Balamurugan Ramar <quic_bramar@quicinc.com>
---
 net/mac80211/rx.c | 3 ++-
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/net/mac80211/rx.c b/net/mac80211/rx.c
index ac018a0..a008a93 100644
--- a/net/mac80211/rx.c
+++ b/net/mac80211/rx.c
@@ -4448,7 +4448,8 @@ static bool ieee80211_rx_data_set_sta(struct ieee80211_rx_data *rx,
 				rx->link = rcu_dereference(rx->sdata->link[sta->deflink.link_id]);
 			} else {
 				rx->link = &rx->sdata->deflink;
-				WARN_ON_ONCE(1);
+				if (!rx->local->in_reconfig)
+					WARN_ON_ONCE(1);
 			}
 		} else {
 			rx->link = &rx->sdata->deflink;
-- 
2.34.1

